reports that he became Bishop of Colophon, a city in Ionia. A Sosthenes
is mentioned also in [Acts xviii.
17](../../../bib/kjv/act018.htm#017.md)<span id="iii.vi.xii-p8.2"></span>,
as ruler of the Jewish synagogue in Corinth. Some wish to identify the
two, supposing the latter to have been afterward converted, but in this
case of course he cannot have been one of the Seventy. Eusebius’
tradition is one in regard to whose value we can form no opinion.

